好想法 -- plugin 的 target 存进 manifest，`install` 时就知道装到哪些 agent。这跟 skills 不一样（skills 的 agent 是运行时选择不存 manifest）。

The user wants:
1. Only 3 targets for plugins (claude-code, cursor, codex)
2. Store the selected targets per-plugin in ai-package.json, so `ai-pkgs install` knows which agents to install each plugin to

This means the manifest entry should include a `targets` field like:
```json
{
  "plugins": {
    "vercel-plugin": {
      "source": "github:vercel/vercel-plugin",
      "version": "main@abc123",
      "path": ".",
      "targets": ["claude-code", "cursor"]
    }
  }
}
```

So unlike skills where agent targets are a runtime choice, plugins need to persist their targets in the manifest since each agent has a different installation process and reproducible installs matter.

